  "text": "and an infinity of one-parameter deformed logarithms can be obtained as particular cases by imposing relationships between the two parameters. In some cases the emerging deformed parameter can be related to the microscopic quantities of the system under inspection. The q-statistical mechanics is recovered, as one-parameter subclass of the two-parameter statistical mechanics, for α = 1 − q and β = 0 whilst, for instance, for α = β = κ, we obtain a new oneparameter subclass of deformed logarithms [CITATION_1] . Therefore, the question of the analytical derivation of the deformed parameter arise also in other context than the q-statistics. To cite an example, the deformed parameter κ has been determined implicitly in [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] by considering the black-hole entropy, obtaining the relation",
